r<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td align="left">
      <h1 style="color:#4A7628;margin:16px;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px;">Welcome to <%= Constant::AppName %>!</h1>
    </td>
    <td align="right">
      <p style="margin:16px;color:#aaa;">
        <%= @user.promotion.current_date.to_s %>
      </p>
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td style="background-color:#f1f7f7" colspan="2">
      <div style="margin:16px">
        <p>
          <%= @user.profile.full_name %>,
        </p>
        
        <p>
          Get ready to move more, eat well, and have fun! Go KP will help you track your healthy activities and the changes you make to feel your best as you work toward your wellness goals.
        </p>
        
        <p>
          <strong>Get started:</strong>
        </p>

        <ul>
          <li style='margin-bottom: 10px;'><strong>Set your daily exercise goal.</strong> Set it once or change it as often as you'd like. Earn points, badges, and other awards each time you achieve it.</li>
          <li style='margin-bottom: 10px;'><strong>Create a long-term goal.</strong> Whether you're managing your weight, drinking more water, eating more vegetables, or training for a race, reaching your long-term goal will motivate you to continually aim higher.</li>
          <li style='margin-bottom: 10px;'><strong>Challenge your co-workers.</strong> Give and get support by challenging yourself and your colleagues to try different activities.</li>
          <li style='margin-bottom: 10px;'><strong>Get social.</strong> Build connections with your colleagues, rate recipies, share tips using Facebook and Twitter, and more.</li>
          <li><strong>Set up your steps-tracking device (optional).</strong> Have a Fitbit<sup>&reg;</sup> or Jawbone<sup>&trade;</sup> device? Sync it with your Go KP account and watch your steps add up... automatically.</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>
          Ready? Then get set and <a href="http://<%= @user.promotion.subdomain + '.' + DomainConfig::DomainNames.first %>">Let's Go KP</a>!
        </p>

        <p>
          <a href="http://<%= @user.promotion.subdomain + '.' + DomainConfig::DomainNames.first %>">http://<%= @user.promotion.subdomain + '.' + DomainConfig::DomainNames.first %></a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>
